      "step_id": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-25T17:34:24.8510000+00:00",
      "source": "user",
      "message": "Good.  Now, it's time to get to work.  We are going to create a new service in this repo.  The service will be described by the most recent version of TypeSpec.  Our ultimate goal will be to generate a Python SDK for it.  None of this will be committed or pushed; we are only testing the local work.  When creating the service, we will use the Azure SDK MCP server to assist us whenever relevant.  The service we create will take GPS coordinates and a date, and will return sunset and sunrise for that location on that date in the timezone which aligns with those GPS coordinates, accounting for local daylight savings time rules.  The caller can optionally specify a city instead of GPS coordinates.  If you need any further clarifications, please ask; otherwise proceed."
    },
