    {
      "step_id": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-25T17:35:29.0580875+00:00",
      "source": "agent",
      "model_name": "claude-haiku-4.5",
      "message": "Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary with all the findings:\n\n## Summary: TypeSpec Project Structure in azure-sdk-tools\n\n### 1. **`specification/` Directory Contents (2 levels deep)**\n\nThe `specification/` directory contains **three example TypeSpec service definitions**:\n\n```\nspecification/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ booklibrary/\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ BookLibrary/          (Book Library Management Service)\nâ”śâ”€â”€ cityfinder/\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ CityFinder/           (City Finder Location Service)\nâ””â”€â”€ diceroller/\n    â””â”€â”€ DiceRoller/           (Dice Roller Service)\n```\n\nEach service has its own directory containing TypeSpec project files.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Example TypeSpec Files (*.tsp)**\n\nThe repository contains **5 .tsp files** demonstrating Azure REST API definitions:\n\n#### **A. Data Plane Services:**\n\n**a) BookLibrary (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\specification\\booklibrary\\BookLibrary\\main.tsp)**\n- Complete CRUD operations for managing a book library\n- Demonstrates: Models, enums, nested objects, pagination, multiple HTTP operations (POST, GET, PATCH, DELETE)\n- Key patterns: `@key` decorator for identifiers, `@minItems` validation, optional fields (`?`)\n\n**b) CityFinder (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\specification\\cityfinder\\CityFinder\\main.tsp)**\n- Location-based service for finding nearby cities\n- Demonstrates: Custom models, validation constraints (`@minValue`, `@maxValue`), POST operations\n- Key patterns: Float types with constraints, request/response models\n\n**c) DiceRoller (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\specification\\diceroller\\DiceRoller\\main.tsp)**\n- Simple dice rolling service with two operations\n- Demonstrates: Array types, minimalistic service definition\n- Key patterns: `@minItems` constraint, multiple operation variants\n\n#### **B. Management Plane Service (Azure Resource Manager):**\n\n**d) Contoso.Management (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\tools\\azsdk-cli\\Azure.Sdk.Tools.Cli.Tests\\TypeSpecTestData\\specification\\testcontoso\\Contoso.Management\\main.tsp)**\n- ARM resource provider example\n- Key patterns: `@armProviderNamespace` decorator, versioning with dependency management\n\n**e) Employee Resource (employee.tsp)**\n- Related model file for Contoso service\n- Demonstrates: `TrackedResource`, `@armResourceOperations`, provisioning state patterns, base64 encoding\n\n---\n\n### 3. **TypeSpec Configuration (tspconfig.yaml)**\n\nAll three main services use similar configurations:\n\n**Example - DiceRoller (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\specification\\diceroller\\DiceRoller\\tspconfig.yaml):**\n\n```yaml\nparameters:\n  \"service-dir\":\n    default: \"sdk/diceroller\"\nemit:\n  - \"@azure-tools/typespec-autorest\"\noptions:\n  \"@azure-tools/typespec-autorest\":\n    emitter-output-dir: \"{project-root}/..\"\n    output-file: \"data-plane/{service-name}/{version-status}/{version}/diceroller.json\"\n  \"@azure-tools/typespec-python\":\n    package-dir: \"azure-diceroller\"\n    namespace: \"azure.diceroller\"\n    generate-test: true\n    generate-sample: true\n    flavor: \"azure\"\nlinter:\n  extends:\n    - \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-rulesets/data-plane\"\n```\n\n**Key Configuration Elements:**\n- **emit**: Specifies emitters (Autorest, Python, etc.)\n- **options**: Emitter-specific settings (package directories, namespaces, output files)\n- **linter**: Uses Azure-specific rulesets (`data-plane` or `resource-manager`)\n- **parameters**: Variables like service directory\n\n**Management Plane (Contoso) adds:**\n- Multiple language emitters (C#, Java, TypeScript, Go)\n- `use-read-only-status-schema` option\n- `azure-resource-provider-folder` structure\n- Specific namespace patterns per language\n\n---\n\n### 4. **main.tsp Structure (Azure REST API Service Definition)**\n\n**Common Pattern in main.tsp:**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Imports\nimport \"@typespec/http\";\nimport \"@typespec/rest\";\nimport \"@typespec/versioning\";\nimport \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\";\n\n// 2. Using declarations\nusing TypeSpec.Http;\nusing TypeSpec.Rest;\nusing TypeSpec.Versioning;\nusing Azure.Core;\n\n// 3. Service decorators\n@service(#{ title: \"Service Name\" })\n@versioned(Azure.ServiceName.Versions)\n@server(\"https://service.azure.com\", \"Service Description\")\nnamespace Azure.ServiceName;\n\n// 4. Version enum\nenum Versions {\n  v2026_03_01_preview: \"2026-03-01-preview\",\n}\n\n// 5. Model definitions\nmodel RequestModel {\n  field: type;\n}\n\n// 6. Route namespace with operations\n@route(\"/endpoint\")\nnamespace OperationNamespace {\n  @post\n  @route(\"/action\")\n  op operation(@body body: RequestModel): ResponseModel;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **TypeSpec Documentation & Templates**\n\nLocated at: **C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\tools\\azsdk-cli\\docs\\specs\\README.md**\n\nThis is a **Design Specification framework** for Azure SDK dev inner loop with stages:\n- 0-Scenarios, 1-Environment Setup, 2-Generating, 3-Customizing, 4-Testing, 5-Samples, 6-Package, 7-Validating, 99-Operations\n\nIncludes spec templates and cross-language considerations.\n\nAdditional TypeSpec tooling docs at: **C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\eng\\common\\tsp-client\\README.md**\n- Explains `@azure-tools/typespec-client-generator-cli` (tsp-client)\n- Usage: `npm exec --prefix {path} -- tsp-client generate --output-dir ./generated`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **TypeSpec Compiler Version**\n\n**Current usage: `\"latest\"`**\n\nFrom package.json files (C:\\Users\\mattge\\source\\repos\\azure-sdk-tools\\specification\\*\\*\\package.json):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@typespec/http\": \"latest\",\n    \"@typespec/rest\": \"latest\",\n    \"@typespec/versioning\": \"latest\",\n    \"@typespec/compiler\": \"latest\",\n    \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\": \"latest\",\n    \"@azure-tools/typespec-autorest\": \"latest\",\n    \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-rulesets\": \"latest\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAll packages use **`\"latest\"` version specifier** (no pinned versions).\n\nThe TypeSpec client generator tool location: `eng/common/tsp-client/` (with Dependabot auto-updates)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Insights:**\n\n1. **Data Plane Pattern**: Simple service models with REST operations, using `@typespec-azure-rulesets/data-plane` linter\n2. **Management Plane Pattern**: Uses `@armProviderNamespace`, `TrackedResource`, `@armResourceOperations`, with resource-manager linter\n3. **Code Generation**: Emits Autorest OpenAPI specs and SDK code for multiple languages (Python, C#, Java, TypeScript, Go)\n4. **Versioning**: All use `@versioned` decorator with enum-based version management\n5. **Namespace Convention**: Azure service names in camelCase under `Azure.*` or `Microsoft.*` namespaces",
