      "message": "TypeSpec compiled successfully and generated the OpenAPI spec. Here's what we have:\n\n**Created files:**\n- `specification/suntimes/SunTimes/main.tsp` â€” service definition\n- `specification/suntimes/SunTimes/tspconfig.yaml` â€” emitter & Python SDK config\n- `specification/suntimes/SunTimes/package.json` â€” TypeSpec dependencies\n- `specification/suntimes/data-plane/preview/2026-03-01-preview/suntimes.json` â€” generated OpenAPI spec\n\n**Service endpoints:**\n- `GET /suntimes/by-coordinates?latitude=...&longitude=...&date=...` â€” sun times by GPS\n- `GET /suntimes/by-city?city=...&date=...` â€” sun times by city name\n\n**Response includes:** sunrise, sunset, IANA timezone, DST status, UTC offset, daylight duration.\n\n2 remaining warnings are acceptable (Azure standard operation templates don't fit custom query ops). Ready to proceed with Python SDK generation â€” shall I use the MCP server's `azsdk_package_generate_code` tool for that?",
