    {
      "step_id": 30,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-25T17:46:47.8390857+00:00",
      "source": "agent",
      "model_name": "claude-haiku-4.5",
      "message": "Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive answer.\n\n## TypeSpec Standard Operations for `use-standard-operations` Linter Rule\n\nBased on my analysis of the typespec-azure-core package, here's everything you need to know about satisfying the `@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core/use-standard-operations` linter rule:\n\n### How the Linter Rule Works\n\n**Location:** `dist/src/rules/use-standard-operations.js`\n\nThe linter **checks that operations derive from the `Azure.Core` namespace**. It passes checks if:\n1. The operation is a template declaration or instance\n2. The operation is defined in the `TypeSpec.Rest.Resource` interface\n3. The operation's signature chain traces back to an `Azure.Core` operation via `sourceOperation`\n\n**Key Code:** Operations must have `sourceOperation.namespace === \"Azure.Core\"` or be templated to satisfy the rule.\n\n---\n\n### Standard Operation Signatures (from `lib/operations.tsp`)\n\nAll operations below are in the `Azure.Core` namespace and satisfy the linter:\n\n#### **RPC Operations (Non-Resource Operations)**\n\n```typescript\n// Basic RPC Operation - for custom GET queries, POST actions without resource context\nop RpcOperation<\n  Parameters extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model,\n  Response extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model,\n  Traits extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model = {},\n  ErrorResponse = Azure.Core.Foundations.ErrorResponse,\n  TraitContexts extends TraitContext = TraitContext.Undefined\n> is Foundations.Operation<...>\n```\n\n**Usage Example:**\n```typescript\nimport \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\";\nusing Azure.Core;\n\nmodel RollRequest {\n  dice: int32[];\n}\n\nmodel RollResult {\n  sum: int32;\n}\n\n@post\n@route(\"/roll\")\nop rollDice is RpcOperation<RollRequest, RollResult>;\n```\n\n---\n\n#### **Long-Running RPC Operation**\n\n```typescript\n@post\nop LongRunningRpcOperation<\n  Parameters extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model,\n  Response extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model,\n  StatusResult extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model,\n  StatusError = Foundations.Error,\n  Traits extends TypeSpec.Reflection.Model = {},\n  ErrorResponse = Azure.Core.Foundations.ErrorResponse,\n  TraitContexts extends TraitContext = TraitContext.Undefined\n> is Foundations.Operation<...>\n```\n\n**Usage:** For long-running POST operations like async jobs or batch processing.\n\n---\n\n#### **Resource Lifecycle Operations** (interface `ResourceOperations`)\n\nThese are defined within the `ResourceOperations<InterfaceTraits, ErrorResponse>` interface:\n\n1. **ResourceRead** â€” GET a single resource\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceRead<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"GET\")\n   ```\n\n2. **ResourceList** â€” GET collection of resources (paginated)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceList<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"GET\")\n   ```\n\n3. **ResourceCreateÂ­OrReplace** â€” PUT (create or replace)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceCreateOrReplace<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"PUT\")\n   ```\n\n4. **ResourceCreateOrUpdate** â€” PATCH (create or update via merge)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceCreateOrUpdate<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"PATCH\")\n   ```\n\n5. **ResourceUpdate** â€” PATCH (update only, not create)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceUpdate<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"PATCH\")\n   ```\n\n6. **ResourceCreateWithÂ­ServiceProvidedName** â€” POST (server generates name)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceCreateWithServiceProvidedName<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"POST\")\n   ```\n\n7. **ResourceDelete** â€” DELETE\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceDelete<Resource, Traits = {}> // @ensureVerb(\"DELETE\")\n   ```\n\n8. **ResourceAction** â€” POST (custom action on a resource)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceAction<Resource, Parameters, Response, Traits = {}> // @action @actionSeparator(\":\")\n   ```\n\n9. **ResourceCollectionÂ­Action** â€” POST (action on collection)\n   ```typescript\n   ResourceCollectionAction<Resource, Parameters, Response, Traits = {}> // @collectionAction\n   ```\n\n10. **GetResourceOperationÂ­Status** â€” GET status of LRO\n    ```typescript\n    GetResourceOperationStatus<Resource, StatusResult = Resource, StatusError = Error, Traits = {}> // @readsResource\n    ```\n\n---\n\n#### **Long-Running Variants**\n\nLong-running versions exist for create, delete, and actions:\n- `LongRunningResourceCreateOrReplace`\n- `LongRunningResourceCreateOrUpdate`\n- `LongRunningResourceDelete`\n- `LongRunningResourceAction`\n- `LongRunningResourceCollectionAction`\n\nAll return `AcceptedResponse` with `LongRunningStatusLocation`.\n\n---\n\n### How to Use Standard Operations\n\n#### **Interface Pattern (Recommended for Resources)**\n\n```typescript\nimport \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\";\nusing Azure.Core;\nusing TypeSpec.Rest;\n\n@resource\nmodel Book {\n  @key(\"bookId\")\n  @segment(\"books\")\n  id: string;\n  \n  title: string;\n  author: string;\n}\n\ninterface Books extends ResourceOperations<{}, ErrorResponse> {\n  @doc(\"Get a book by ID\")\n  read: ResourceRead<Book>;\n  \n  @doc(\"List all books\")\n  list: ResourceList<Book>;\n  \n  @doc(\"Create a book\")\n  create: ResourceCreateOrReplace<Book>;\n  \n  @doc(\"Update a book\")\n  update: ResourceUpdate<Book>;\n  \n  @doc(\"Delete a book\")\n  delete: ResourceDelete<Book>;\n}\n```\n\n#### **Standalone Operation Pattern**\n\n```typescript\nimport \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\";\nusing Azure.Core;\n\nmodel FindCityRequest {\n  latitude: float64;\n  longitude: float64;\n}\n\nmodel CityResult {\n  name: string;\n  population: int32;\n}\n\n@post\n@route(\"/cities/find-nearest\")\nop findNearestCity is RpcOperation<FindCityRequest, CityResult>;\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n1. **Import the library:**\n   ```typescript\n   import \"@azure-tools/typespec-azure-core\";\n   using Azure.Core;\n   ```\n\n2. **For custom operations:** Use `RpcOperation` or `LongRunningRpcOperation`\n\n3. **For resource operations:** Use `ResourceOperations<InterfaceTraits, ErrorResponse>` interface with the standard operation templates\n\n4. **Traits:** Pass optional custom traits for conditional requests, repeatable requests, client request IDs, etc.\n\n---\n\n### What Operations Violate the Rule\n\nâťŚ Raw operation declarations without deriving from Azure.Core:\n```typescript\n// FAILS the linter\n@post\nop myCustomOperation(body: MyRequest): MyResponse;\n```\n\nâś… Fixed by using standard operations:\n```typescript\n// PASSES the linter\nop myCustomOperation is RpcOperation<MyRequest, MyResponse>;\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Use Case | Operation | HTTP Verb |\n|----------|-----------|-----------|\n| Custom GET query or POST action (non-resource) | `RpcOperation` | Any |\n| Long-running custom action | `LongRunningRpcOperation` | POST |\n| Read single resource | `ResourceRead` | GET |\n| List resources | `ResourceList` | GET |\n| Create/Replace | `ResourceCreateOrReplace` | PUT |\n| Create/Update via merge | `ResourceCreateOrUpdate` | PATCH |\n| Update only | `ResourceUpdate` | PATCH |\n| Custom action on resource | `ResourceAction` | POST |\n| Delete resource | `ResourceDelete` | DELETE |\n| Check LRO status | `GetResourceOperationStatus` | GET |\n\nAll operations in `Azure.Core` namespace satisfy the linter rule automatically.",
